{"lemma":"سِتْرَيْ","slug":"سِتْرَيْ","root":"س.ت.ر","root_slug":"س-ت-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ت-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سِتْر","root":"ستر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18853","","n18856","n18857"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%90%D8%AA%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cover, to hide, to screen; to veil"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to protect, to shield, to guard, to safeguard; to shelter"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to protect, to shield, to guard, to safeguard; to shelter; to marry off (a girl or a young woman) (as in order to protect her from sin)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cover up, to hide, to screen; to enveil","examples":[{"text":"فَجَعَلَ ٱبْنُ ٱلزُّبَيْرِ أَعْمِدَةً فَسَتَّرَ عَلَيْهَا ٱلسُّتُور حَتَّى ٱرْتَفَعَ بِنَاؤُهُ","english":"And Ibn Az-Zubayr made pillars and covered them with curtains to further the building’s erection."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to protect, to shield, to guard, to safeguard; to shelter"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to protect, to shield, to guard, to safeguard; to shelter; to marry off (a girl or a young woman) (as in order to protect her from sin)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a covering or barrier that shelters and protects or restricts","examples":[{"text":"هَتَكَ اللهُ سِتْرَ الرَّجُلِ","english":"Allah exposed the man [and his deeds]. (literally \"Allah tore the man's cover.\")"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a covering or barrier that shelters and protects or restricts; curtain, drape","examples":[{"text":"فَجَعَلَ ٱبْنُ ٱلزُّبَيْرِ أَعْمِدَةً فَسَتَّرَ عَلَيْهَا ٱلسُّتُورَ حَتَّى ٱرْتَفَعَ بِنَاؤُهُ","english":"And Ibn Az-Zubayr made pillars and covered them up with curtains to further the building’s erection."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a covering or barrier that shelters and protects or restricts; shame, scruple; compunction","tags":["figuratively"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of سُتْرَة (sutra)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of سِتَار (sitār)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of سِتْر (sitr)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew סֵתֶר (“hiddenness; secrecy”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18853","headword_ar":"سَتَرَ","root":"str","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"satorN","text_ar":"سَتْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"satarN","text_ar":"سَتَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, veiled, concealed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing; (M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covered it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"st~r","text_ar":"ستّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same, (M,) [or has an intensive sense, or denotes frequency or repetition of the action, or its application to many objects: accord. to Golius, “"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sub velo, obtenso eo"},{"kind":"text","text":"[sic],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ne quis vir intueretur eam, custodivit"},{"kind":"text","text":"puellam: et"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clam asservavit habuitque"},{"kind":"text","text":"eam: ” as on the authority of the KL: in which I find nothing of the kind but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasotiyrN","text_ar":"تَسْتِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. by the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dr Prdh dA$tn","text_ar":"در پرده داشتن"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to have"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hold, within a curtain."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He protected"},{"kind":"text","text":"another. (The Lexicons passim.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saturato","text_ar":"سَتُرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sataArapN","text_ar":"سَتَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"satiyrap","text_ar":"سَتِيرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"modest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bashful."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"satura","text_ar":"سَتُرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sitorN","text_ar":"سِتْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, intelligent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A"]},{"entry_id":"n18856","headword_ar":"سِتْرٌ","root":"str","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sutorapN","text_ar":"سُتْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which latter see also below] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sitaArapN","text_ar":"سِتَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sitaArN","text_ar":"سِتَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"satarapN","text_ar":"سَتَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isotaArN","text_ar":"اـِسْتَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isotaArapN","text_ar":"اـِسْتَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) which last is only known to occur in one instance, in a trad., (M, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misotarN","text_ar":"مِسْتَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything by which a person or thing is veiled, concealed, hidden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covered; a veil; a curtain; a screen; a cover; a covering; a covert;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K:) [and the first and second,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything by which one is protected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sheltered:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sitorN","text_ar":"سِتْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sutuwrN","text_ar":"سُتُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asotaArN","text_ar":"اَسْتَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) [the latter a pl. of pauc.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suturN","text_ar":"سُتُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, TA;) which last is also pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sitaArN","text_ar":"سِتَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kutubN","text_ar":"كُتُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kitaAbN","text_ar":"كِتَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sitaArapN","text_ar":"سِتَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sataAy^iru","text_ar":"سَتَايِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) ↓ [Hence the phrase]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hataka A@ll~`hu sitorahu","text_ar":"هَتَكَ ا@للّٰهُ سِتْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God rent open,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God rend open, his veil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covering;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God manifested,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God manifest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"make known, his vices,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faults:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God disgraced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dishonoured, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exposed him to disgrace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dishonour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God disgrace"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dishonour him"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a All~ayolu A^asotaArahu","text_ar":"مَدَّ اللَّيْلُ اَسْتَارَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Night spread its curtains"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ayoli","text_ar":"اللَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amud~u A_ilaY A@ll~`hi yadaY~a taHota sitaAri","text_ar":"اَمُدُّ اـِلَى ا@للّٰهِ يَدَىَّ تَحْتَ سِتَارِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I stretch forth my hands"},{"kind":"text","text":"in supplication"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to God beneath the veil of night"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sitorN","text_ar":"سِتْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [Because by it one protects himself from the displeasure of God. See 8.] And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Modesty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bashfulness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA lifulaAnK sitorN wa laA HijorN","text_ar":"مَا لِفُلَانٍ سِتْرٌ وَ لَا حِجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one has not modesty nor intelligence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Intelligence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqolN","text_ar":"عَقْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) In the K it is explained by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamalN","text_ar":"عَمَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this appears to be a mistranscription, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqolN","text_ar":"عَقْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","TA","A"]},{"entry_id":"n18857","headword_ar":"سَتَرٌ","root":"str","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A shield."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}